yAfQeKdK4k4g_aPsGVg_QWXPm_4J68r5dtcupdxxzrfzWVG7SKUDXbpM5j29ZWHnWGLfAiGfq0Pqp_tCyCpJiLqdqLJ8bw63RyfrXJpBwdvsaxwUIksT7AUpXzEb7qsJQtwyH2J-umdrlxeEnPmhZ3YfkHTEgMAUWiQSXqqW-mpQalTtJ-ZNfk0zvskXjgBL7_8S0nmWvejMx_TpwLTCZMueVtTFRtSHZUGUa_IrUgqVolfeBoT0MN10nsPUz5yIfuus97sL3DHLBXtHyaz5h6L0bFVBwwwZcUMS8xfWBi0cSGSuJH4QgxvgqbVAUSrq9FJE=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JDK entropy source**\\n\\nI’m contemplating how to handle a fallback failure regarding the JDK's initial entropy source. It doesn’t seem to be a \\\"known bug,\\\" but rather an environment-dependent issue. I could phrase it neutrally by configuring the DRBG to utilize the JDK's initial-entropy-source discovery path. I might try using SecureRandom.getInstance with the provider. If that fails due to the JDK's encapsulation, I should check if the exception chain includes an IllegalAccessException.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Restoring properties**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to restore properties. It seems like `Security.setProperty` can't remove them if the original value is null. Maybe the way to go is to set it to an empty value instead?  It's a bit unclear, but I wonder if that would work effectively. I need to look into this more to be sure I'm approaching it correctly and not missing something important!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering implementation details**\\n\\nI'm thinking that perhaps the algorithm can instantiate a provider implementation using reflection in the Java Cryptography Architecture (JCA). Additionally, Native Image might require some service metadata from the provider. I wonder if the generated bytes could block the fallback for `IncrementalEntropySourceProvider` in CoreSecureRandom, which could make seed generation slow. But 16 bytes should be sufficient, right? It feels like there’s a lot to unpack here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_bsHFsT8GlGDQDLF1aIqCHNTU|fc_0eb6df6e03b175a4016a25eb19f0f88196aaa5324abe42c7a9", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk18on/DRBGTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk18on;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.BouncyCastleProvider;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.parallel.ResourceLock;\n\nimport java.security.Provider;\nimport java.security.SecureRandom;\nimport java.security.Security;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class DRBGTest {\n    private static final String RANDOM_SOURCE_PROPERTY = \"securerandom.source\";\n    private static final String STRONG_ALGORITHMS_PROPERTY = \"securerandom.strongAlgorithms\";\n    private static final String INVALID_RANDOM_SOURCE_URL = \"not-a-url\";\n    private static final String UNAVAILABLE_STRONG_ALGORITHM = \"NoSuchAlgorithm:SUN\";\n\n    @Test\n    @ResourceLock(\"java.security.Security\")\n    void generatesDefaultSecureRandomBytesUsingInitialEntropySourceDiscovery() throws Exception {\n        String originalRandomSource = requireSecurityProperty(RANDOM_SOURCE_PROPERTY);\n        String originalStrongAlgorithms = requireSecurityProperty(STRONG_ALGORITHMS_PROPERTY);\n\n        try {\n            Security.setProperty(RANDOM_SOURCE_PROPERTY, INVALID_RANDOM_SOURCE_URL);\n            Security.setProperty(STRONG_ALGORITHMS_PROPERTY, UNAVAILABLE_STRONG_ALGORITHM);\n\n            Provider provider = new BouncyCastleProvider();\n            SecureRandom random = SecureRandom.getInstance(\"DEFAULT\", provider);\n            byte[] generated = new byte[16];\n            random.nextBytes(generated);\n\n            assertThat(random.getAlgorithm()).isEqualTo(\"DEFAULT\");\n            assertThat(random.getProvider().getName()).isEqualTo(BouncyCastleProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\n            assertThat(generated).hasSize(16);\n        } finally {\n            Security.setProperty(RANDOM_SOURCE_PROPERTY, originalRandomSource);\n            Security.setProperty(STRONG_ALGORITHMS_PROPERTY, originalStrongAlgorithms);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static String requireSecurityProperty(String propertyName) {\n        String propertyValue = Security.getProperty(propertyName);\n        assertThat(propertyValue).isNotNull();\n        return propertyValue;\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 431, "output": 2530, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31633, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780869871091, "responseId": "resp_0eb6df6e03b175a4016a25eaefb3448196b1fffa334c27c02a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_bsHFsT8GlGDQDLF1aIqCHNTU|fc_0eb6df6e03b175a4016a25eb19f0f88196aaa5324abe42c7a9", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2309 bytes to tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk18on/DRBGTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780869919211}]}
